  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="sonnet">
   <l>GRaunt me smooth vtt'rance Muses to reherse</l>
   <l>The pleasing smoothnesse of thy worthy verse:</l>
   <l>If there be words fram'd by admired wits</l>
   <l>To sing thy praise, those words my verse befits,</l>
   <l>But such are scant, and there's not one remaines</l>
   <l>Can giue thee due, none worth enough containes.</l>
   <l>To sing thy praise in an vp-raised straine,</l>
   <l>And giue desert to thy admired paine:</l>
   <l>Feare not the censure of each babbling tongue,</l>
   <l>They care not whom they pleasure, whom they wrong:</l>
   <l>Respect it not if fooles thy Muse miscall,</l>
   <l>Thy paine, her worth deserues applause of all:</l>
   <l>In whose adoring if my pen offends,</l>
   <l>My heart my pens defaults will make amends.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>Z.D.</signed>
   </closer>
</div>
